Kim Jong Il Greets Roh Moo Hyun 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 2 (KCNA) -- General Secretary Kim Jong Il on Tuesday greeted south Korean President Roh Moo Hyun on a visit to Pyongyang. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The streets of the capital city were wrapped in a festive mood. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The meeting of the top leaders of the north and the south will mark an event of weighty significance in boosting the inter-Korean relations to a new higher stage on the basis of the historic June 15 North-South Joint Declaration and in the spirit of "By our nation itself" and opening up a new phase for achieving peace on the Korean Peninsula, prosperity common to the nation and national reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Pyongyangites from all walks of life lined up at the plaza in front of the April 25 House of Culture where flags of the DPRK were seen fluttering. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 When Kim Jong Il appeared at the plaza, the crowd broke into thunderous cheers of "Hurrah!" rocking the earth and sky. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there were Kim Yong Il, premier of the Cabinet, Kim Il Chol, minister of the People's Armed Forces, Choe Thae Bok, chairman of the Supreme People's Assembly, Yang Hyong Sop, vice-president of the SPA Presidium, Kim Ki Nam, secretary of the Central Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea, Kang Sok Ju, first vice-minister of Foreign Affairs, Kim Yong Dae, chairman of the Central Committee of the Korean Social Democratic Party, and leading officials of the party, armed forces and power organs, working people's organizations, ministries and national institutions. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At noon, a limousine carrying Kim Yong Nam, president of the SPA Presidium, and President Roh Moo Hyun arrived at the plaza after passing through tens of ri-long route amid the welcome of the crowd. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Amidst the playing of the welcome music, the crowd welcomed Roh Moo Hyun, waving bouquets. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Jong Il exchanged a handshake and greetings with Roh Moo Hyun. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Roh Moo Hyun is accompanied by Minister of Finance and Economy Kwon O Gyu, Minister of Science and Technology Kim U Sik, Minister of Unification Ri Jae Jong, Minister of National Defence Kim Jang Su, Minister of Agriculture and Forestry Im Sang Gyu, Minister of Health and Welfare Pyon Jae Jin, Director of the National Intelligence Service Kim Man Bok and other suite members and reporters. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A function took place at the plaza in welcome of Roh Moo Hyun. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Jong Il and Roh Moo Hyun reviewed the guard of honor of the three services of the Korean People's Army. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Women workers presented bouquets to Roh Moo Hyun and his wife. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Jong Il and Roh Moo Hyun waved back to the enthusiastically welcoming crowd, passing before them.

Talks Held between Kim Yong Nam and Roh Moo Hyun  
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 2 (KCNA) -- Talks were held between President of the Presidium of the Supreme People's Assembly Kim Yong Nam and south Korean President Roh Moo Hyun at the Mansudae Assembly Hall Tuesday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there from the DPRK side were Kim Il Chol, minister of the People's Armed Forces, Choe Thae Bok, chairman of the Supreme People's Assembly, Ro Tu Chol, vice-premier of the Cabinet, Kim Yong Sam, minister of Railways, Ra Tong Hui, minister of Land and Marine Transport, Choe Chang Sik, minister of Public Health, Ri Kyong Sik, minister of Agriculture, and officials concerned and from the south side Minister of Finance and Economy Kwon O Gyu, Minister of Science and Technology Kim U Sik, Minister of Unification Ri Jae Jong, Minister of National Defence Kim Jang Su, Minister of Agriculture and Forestry Im Sang Gyu, Minister of Health and Welfare Pyon Jae Jin, Director of the National Intelligence Service Kim Man Bok and other suite members.

Banquet Given for Roh Moo Hyun  
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 2 (KCNA) -- Kim Yong Nam, president of the Presidium of the Supreme People's Assembly, and Pak Kwan O, chairman of the Pyongyang City People's Committee, hosted a banquet at the Mokran House Tuesday in honor of south Korean President Roh Moo Hyun and his party on a visit to Pyongyang. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there on invitation together with Roh Moo Hyun were Minister of Finance and Economy Kwon O Gyu, Minister of Science and Technology Kim U Sik, Minister of Unification Ri Jae Jong, Minister of National Defence Kim Jang Su, Minister of Agriculture and Forestry Im Sang Gyu, Minister of Health and Welfare Pyon Jae Jin, Director of the National Intelligence Service Kim Man Bok and other suite members. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On hand were Choe Thae Bok, chairman of the Supreme People's Assembly, Ro Tu Chol, vice-premier of the Cabinet, Kim Yong Dae, chairman of the Central Committee of the Korean Social Democratic Party, officials of power bodies, working people's organizations, ministries and national institutions and officials concerned. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Yong Nam in a speech made at the banquet recalled that the meeting of the top leaders of the north and the south that took place in Pyongyang seven years ago to produce the June 15 joint declaration marked a historic event that demonstrated to the world the will of the Korean nation for reunification, saying that the idea of "By our nation itself" is a common desire of the nation as it indicates the way of achieving reconciliation, unity, reunification and prosperity. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We are faced with a sacred task of further developing the inter-Korean relations to open up a new phase of national reunification, he noted, adding it is a noble mission for all members of the nation to fulfil the task. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Saying that attaching importance to the nation and pooling efforts guarantee a prospect of reunification and prosperity, he expressed the expectation that the current meeting of the top leaders of the north and south would bring fresh hope and happiness to all Koreans desirous of national reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Roh Moo Hyun in a speech expressed sincere thanks for the warm welcome accorded to him and his party by compatriots in the north. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 I realized once again that the land of Korea, though partitioned, still retains its appearance as one and the same country and the compatriots in the north are of the same nation, he said, referring to the efforts exerted by the south and the north to build confidence over the past seven years since the publication of the June 15 joint declaration. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He expressed the expectation that promoting confidence would serve as a foundation for consolidating peace on the Korean Peninsula and carving out the future of prosperity common to the nation and this meeting would mark an occasion to do so. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He prayed for peace and prosperity on the peninsula where reconciliation and cooperation have become a trend and eternal development of the nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He wished Chairman of the National Defence Commission Kim Jong Il good health.

Roh Moo Hyun Welcomed by Pyongyangites along Route  
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 2 (KCNA) -- South Korean President Roh Moo Hyun arrived in Pyongyang Tuesday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At 11:40 a.m. a motorcade carrying Roh Moo Hyun and his party reached the road in front of the People's Palace of Culture. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Roh Moo Hyun was greeted by Kim Yong Nam, president of the Presidium of the Supreme People's Assembly, Choe Yong Rim, secretary general of the SPA Presidium, and Pak Kwan O, chairman of the Pyongyang City People's Committee. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Women workers presented bouquets to Roh Moo Hyun and his wife. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Roh Moo Hyun waved back to the crowd shouting "Welcome." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A limousine carrying Kim Yong Nam and Roh Moo Hyun passed through Mansudae Street, Changjon Intersection and Chilsongmun Street. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Hundreds of thousands of Pyongyangites welcomed Roh Moo Hyun along the route, waving bouquets and chanting slogan "National Reunification."

Wife of Roh Moo Hyun and Suite Members Visit Different Places 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 2 (KCNA) -- Kwon Ryang Suk, wife of south Korean President Roh Moo Hyun, and some suite members from the south side visited the Grand People's Study House Tuesday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 She looked round several reading rooms, lecture rooms and other places of the house. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Earlier, she had a talk with women from all walks of life in the north. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Meanwhile, suite members of the president visited the E-Library of Kim Chaek University of Technology. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They went round with keen interest reading rooms, remote controlled lecture rooms and others.

Expansion and Development of South-South Cooperation Urged 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 2 (KCNA) -- It is the consistent stand of the DPRK to expand and develop South-South cooperation, declared Choe Su Hon, vice-minister of Foreign Affairs, who was heading the DPRK delegation, on September 27 at the meeting of foreign ministers of the Group of 77 held on the sidelines of the 62nd session of the UN General Assembly. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Manifesting the view of the delegation on the meeting's purport of defining the common stand of the G-77 toward the main agenda items of the economic and social fields which were brought up for discussion at the 62nd session of the UN General Assembly, he said: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The G-77 should make the common actions of the developing countries against the unilateral and strong-arm practices in the economic and social fields more organized and strengthened and continue to orchestrate the efforts to expand and boost South-South cooperation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It should promote the expansion and development of South-South cooperation, keeping hold on this as its unswerving policy guideline and enhance its capacity of collective action as the champion of the interests of the developing countries in multilateral negotiating arenas. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Showing deep interest in boosting South-South cooperation, the DPRK government has devoted disinterested support and efforts, zealously involving itself in the Non-Aligned Movement and the activities of the G-77 and the United Nations system. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK government, true to its commitments at the Second South Summit, initiated cooperation programs in different realms such as agriculture, bioscience, standardization and measurement for a number of developing countries in Asia and Africa and has made governmental efforts for their implementation this year, too, following last year and gained good experience and results in this course. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK will make in the future, too, an active contribution to the building of a peaceful and prosperous independent world by fulfilling its obligation and duty in establishing a new international economic order based on justice, equality and impartiality and further expanding and developing South-South cooperation based on collective self-reliance.

Eradication of Racism and Racial Discrimination Called for  
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 2 (KCNA) -- The government of the DPRK will join the international community in its efforts to build a new world free from racism and racial discrimination and do all it can to achieve the objective, declared a DPRK delegate addressing the 6th meeting of the UN Human Rights Council on Sept. 25. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Noting that racism has not yet been eradicated though six years have passed since the UN anti-racism conference was held in Durban of South Africa, he emphasized this is chiefly attributable to the lack of the proper settlement of past wrongs. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The international community at the Durban conference urged those states that institutionally perpetrated the crimes related to racism and racial discrimination in the past to admit their responsibilities for them and pay due compensation and reparation to the states, communities and individuals that suffered them but this just demand has still been ignored, he said and went on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Korea was subjected to severe national discrimination and unbearable humiliation for over four decades under the military occupation of Japanese imperialism. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In that period more than 8.4 million Koreans were forcibly drafted, over one million Koreans were killed and 200,000 Korean women were forced into sexual slavery for the Imperial Japanese Army. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Moreover, Koreans were forced to change their own names into Japanese ones and use Japanese instead of Korean. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The above-mentioned crimes have not yet been redeemed even in this new century and the international community is increasingly worried about the possible reoccurrence of those crimes. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Korean residents in Japan, descendants of the Koreans who were taken to Japan during its colonial rule over Korea, are subjected to harsh suppression and discrimination in all aspects such as education, healthcare and employment for the mere reason that they are Koreans and citizens of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Such actions cannot be justified under any circumstances but should be halted at once.

Greetings to German President 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 2 (KCNA) -- Kim Yong Nam, president of the Presidium of the DPRK Supreme People's Assembly, sent a message of greetings to Horst Kohler, President of the Federal Republic of Germany, on the occasion of its national day on Monday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Expressing the belief that the relations between the DPRK and Germany would steadily grow stronger by common efforts, the message wholeheartedly wished the German president greater success in his responsible work for the prosperity of the country.

Greetings to President of Cyprus
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 2 (KCNA) -- Kim Yong Nam, president of the Presidium of the DPRK Supreme People's Assembly, sent a message of greetings to Tassos Papadopoulos, President of Cyprus, on Monday on the occasion of the 47th anniversary of its independence. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Expressing the belief that the relations between the DPRK and Cyprus would grow stronger in line with the desire and interests of the two peoples, Kim in the message wished the president success in his responsible work for development of the country.

Anniversary of Kim Jong Il's Work Observed
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 2 (KCNA) -- Kim Jong Il made public his famous work "The Workers' Party of Korea Is the Party of the Great Leader Comrade Kim Il Sung" on October 2, Juche 84 (1995). This was the declaration of his firm will to always advance the Korean revolution as intended and expected by President Kim Il Sung. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Rodong Sinmun Tuesday says this in a signed article. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Jong Il in the work systematized and comprehensively dealt with the President's Juche-oriented idea of building a party and the exploits performed by him. And he also clarified the principled issues arising in developing the WPK into an eternal party of the President. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The ideas and theories expounded by Kim Jong Il in his work have served as fundamental guidelines for building the WPK and the party's activities over the past 12 years, the article says, and goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is the true picture of the WPK as the party of the President that it is regarding his revolutionary idea as the steadfast guiding idea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The President's revolutionary idea is the monolithic guiding idea of the WPK and an invincible banner of the Korean revolution. Neither the WPK shining with his august name nor the victory of the Juche-oriented cause of Songun would be thinkable without the President's revolutionary idea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The invincible might of the WPK as the party of the President finds its manifestation in that it has always preserved the steel-strong unity and cohesion of the whole party at a high level. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The strong organization, high sense of discipline and conscious and revolutionary way of the party life that prevail in the WPK today clearly testify to its unity in the Songun era. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The might of the WPK's unity growing stronger than ever before in the Songun era is the brilliant fruition of Kim Jong Il's tested leadership. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The high leadership authority of the WPK as the party of the President lies in the fact that it is making dynamic advance after forming an integral whole with the people, deeply rooted among them. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Party devotedly serves the people while they repose absolute trust in it. Herein lie the inexhaustible might of the WPK and its rosy future.

International Trade Fair to Be Held 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 2 (KCNA) -- The 3rd Pyongyang Autumn International Trade Fair will be held at the Three-Revolution Exhibition from October 8 to 11. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  It will bring together companies of the DPRK, China, Russia, Netherlands, Germany, Mongolia, Belgium, Switzerland, Australia, Britain, Italy, Vietnam, France, Finland, Poland and Taipei of China. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Exhibited there will be machine tools, electric and electronic equipment, vehicles, petrochemicals, medicaments, daily necessities, foodstuffs and others. The fair will mark an occasion in boosting the economic cooperation and exchange among countries and regions.

New Technology for Frog Proliferation and Breeding Developed
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 2 (KCNA) -- The Biological Faculty of Kim Hyong Jik University of Education has succeeded in the research of mass-proliferating the Rana temporaria ornativentris. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Rana temporaria ornativentris which belongs to edible frog family not only eats harmful insects two times that of other kinds of frogs but also is a good drug-stuff. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Teachers and researchers of the faculty completed the technology to remarkably raise the rate of the female Rana temporaria ornativentris under the condition of artificial breeding. They have thus boosted the propagating rate to more than 70 percent from two percent of natural ecology. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 And they have realized the intensive breeding of over 5,000 Rana temporaria ornativentris in a place covering tens of square meters and solved fodder problem. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The technology of artificial proliferation and breeding will make it possible to provide larger amount of drug-stuff for health and be conducive to protecting forests and farm crops.

DPRK's Birthday Celebrated
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 2 (KCNA) -- The Association for Friendship with the Korean People headquartered in Spain posted a special write-up carrying a portrait of President Kim Il Sung on its Internet homepage "One Korea Network" on the occasion of the 59th birthday of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The article of the homepage titled "True country for people" said that the founding of the DPRK meant the appearance of a true people's country in Korea and it has stood as an invulnerable fortress protecting the destiny of the people by its powerful military forces. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Noting that the DPRK has greeted the heyday in its development, demonstrating its dignity as a sovereign state, the article stressed that this has been possible thanks to the leadership of Kim Il Sung who consistently bolstered the national defence capability with Songun. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Thanks to the Songun politics being pursued by Kim Jong Il the might of the DPRK has been further augmented, the article noted, adding that the DPRK would always prosper as it serves the people and is indisputably supported and trusted by them.

DPRK's Birthday Marked 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 2 (KCNA) -- A total of more than 200 multifarious events were held by political parties and organizations in more than 60 countries in celebration of the 59th birthday of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The participants of the events highly praised the undying feats of the peerlessly great persons, unanimously saying that the history of Korea is a history of the wise guidance of President Kim Il Sung and Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At least 100 media organizations of different countries widely introduced the ever-victorious history, advantages and invincible might of Songun Korea which has always remained shining along with the august names of the peerlessly great persons. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Bangladeshi newspaper Blits, the newspaper of Hong Kong of China Ching Pao, the Russian newspaper Patriot and other media gave wide publicity to articles interwoven with the portraits of the peerlessly great persons and photos showing their revolutionary activities. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Institutions and organizations in various countries posted on their Internet homepages articles titled "President Kim Il Sung's feats in nation-building," "Songun policy and Korean-style socialism", "Songun Korea will always remain shining", "Genuine country for people" and others or issued information bulletins.

Kim Jong Il recibe a Roh Moo Hyun
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, 2 de octubre (ATCC) -- El Dirigente Kim Jong Il, Secretario General del Partido del Trabajo de Corea y Presidente del Comite de Defensa Nacional de la Republica Popular Democratica de Corea, recibio este martes al presidente Roh Moo Hyun quien hace una visita a Pyongyang. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Las calles de la capital estaban enueltas en ambiente de bienvenida.  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@El encuentro de los maximos dirigentes del Norte y el Sur de Corea tendra una gran significacion en ampliar y desarrollar en la etapa mas alta las relaciones bilaterales a base de la historica Declaracion Conjunta Norte-Sur del 15 de Junio y el espiritu de "entre nosotros, los connacionales" y abrir una nueva coyuntura para la paz de la Peninsula Coreana, la prosperidad comun de la nacion y la reunificacion de la patria. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  En la explanada de la Casa Cultural 25 de Abril donde flameaba la bandera de la RPDC estaban enfilados los ciudadanos de distintos estratos. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Al aparecer el Dirigente en la plaza, estallaron las estruendosas aclamaciones de "!Hurra!" que estremecian el cielo y la tierra. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Figuraban alli el primer ministro del Consejo de Ministros Kim Yong Il, el ministro de las Fuerzas Armadas Populares Kim Il Chol, el presidente de la Asamblea Popular Suprema Choe Thae Bok, el vicepresidente del Presidium de la APS Yang Hyong Sop, el secretario del CC del PTC Kim Ki Nam, el primer vicecanciller Kang Sok Ju, el presidente del CC del Partido Social-Democrata de Corea Kim Yong Dae y otros funcionarios directivos de los organismos del partido, las fuerzas armadas y el Poder, entidades de masas, ministerios y organos centrales. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@A mediodia, el carro descapotable, en que viajaban el presidente del Presidium de la Asamblea Popular Suprema, Kim Yong Nam, y el presidente Roh Moo Hyun, llego a la explanada tras recorrer una ruta de decenas de ries (10 ries equivalen a 4 kilometros) donde estaban enfilados los habitantes para dar la bienvenida. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Mientras se interpretaba la musica de la ocasion, los habitantes dieron la bienvenida al presidente Roh agitando ramos de flores. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  El Dirigente Kim Jong Il y el presidente Roh Moo Hyun se saludaron tras un apreton de manos. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Acompanaron a Roh, el ministro de Finanzas y Economia, Kwon O Gyu, el ministro de la Ciencia y la Tecnologia Kim U Sik, el ministro de Reunificacion Ri Jae Jong, el ministro de Defensa Nacional Kim Jang Su, el ministro de Agricultura y Silvicultura Im Sang Gyu, el ministro de Salud Publica y Bienestar Pyon Jae Jin, el director del Servicio Nacional de Inteligencia Kim Man Bok, y otros acompanantes asi como los periodistas. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  En la explanada tuvo lugar una ceremonia de bienvenida en honor del presidente Roh. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  El Dirigente Kim Jong Il y el presidente Roh Moo Hyun pasaron revista a la guardia de honor de las fuerzas terrestres, navales y aereas del Ejercito Popular de Corea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Trabajadoras obsequiaron ramos de flores al matrimonio de Roh. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Los dos maximos dirigentes respondieron al hospitalario saludo de la multitud pasando por delante de ella.

Conversaciones entre Kim Yong Nam y Roh Moo Hyun
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, 2 de octubre (ATCC) -- El presidente del Presidium de la Asamblea Popular Suprema, Kim Yong Nam, y el presidente Roh Moo Hyun sostuvieron conversaciones este martes en el capitalino Palacio de los Congresos Mansudae. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  En la ocasion estuvieron presentes por la parte Norte el ministro de las Fuerzas Armadas Populares Kim Il Chol, el presidente de la Asamblea Popular Suprema Choe Thae Bok, el vicepremier del Consejo de Ministros Ro Tu Chol, el ministro del Ferrocarril Kim Yong Sam, el ministro del Transporte Automovilistico y Maritimo Ra Tong Hui, el ministro de Salud Publica Choe Chang Sik, el ministro de Agricultura Ri Kyong Sik y otros funcionarios. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
